What I don&#x27;t see is these three statements:<p>1. Force Lavabit to provide their private SSL keys and route all their traffic through a government machine that performed a man-in-the-middle style data collection;  
2. Change their software to subvert Lavabits own security measures and log emails after SSL decryption but before encrypting with the users public keys; or  
3. Require Lavabit to install malicious code to infect their own customers with government-supplied malware.<p>It sounds like he already has the ability to comply with demands for information. I don&#x27;t see where this new stipulation by them requires any meaningful change to his existing infrastructure.
